HAVANA, Nov. 1 (Xinhua) -- Cuba's news agency Prensa Latina on Monday launched a new web portal. Norge Lopez, an engineer at the Department of Technical Development of Prensa Latina, said that the new portal will provide the readers with interactive tools and a more attractive graphic design. "We have made changes in keeping with the international media standards to better reach our audiences," he said, adding that "the website features podcasts, video stories, and photos." Founded in 1959, Prensa Latina now has 40 offices across the world and a Havana-based multimedia center with the capacity to process 400 dispatches in six different languages daily. Enditem